      "delete_workflow_instance": false,
      "description": "Posts a message with an Adaptive Card to a Microsoft Teams channel using a webhook. Note that you must create a webhook in Teams before you can use this atomic.\n\nTarget: HTTP endpoint for your webhook. For example, the host might be \"your-tenant.webhook.office.com\" and the path would be everything after the first \"/\"\n\nAccount Key: None\n\nSteps:\n[] Build the JSON for the message and card\n[] Send the message to the webhook\n[] Check if the request succeeded:\n[]\u003e If it didn't, output an error\n[]\u003e If it did, check that the webhook accepted the message (if not, output an error)\n\nInteractive card designer: https://adaptivecards.io/designer/\n\nMore information about webhooks in Teams: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/platform/webhooks-and-connectors/how-to/connectors-using#setting-up-a-custom-incoming-webhook",
